Class Route

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrix.sdk.model.Route
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable

    public abstract class Route
extends Object
implements Parcelable
    Represents a route, containing information such as travel times, distance, and maneuvers.

      • getAbnormalityMinutes

        public abstract int getAbnormalityMinutes()
        Gets the difference in minutes between the travel time for the route and the normal travel time expected for the time and day.

        abnormalityMinutes is calculated as the predicted travel time for the route minus the typical travel time for the time and day. If the route is faster than typical, then abnormalityMinutes will be negative. Note that it is not the difference between free flow traffic time and predicted travel time, but rather the travel time that uses typical levels of congestion for time and day.

        Returns:
        The difference in minutes between the travel time and the normal travel time expected.

      • getTravelTimeMinutes

        public abstract int getTravelTimeMinutes()
        Gets the currently calculated travel time in minutes.

        If there are any road closures on the route, this value will be -1.

        Returns:
        The currently calculated travel time, or -1 if there is a road closure.

      • getRouteQuality

        public abstract int getRouteQuality()
        Gets the quality of the route, typically scaled from 0 (most congested) to 3 (least congested).

        The following table describes the route quality values:

        Value Description Travel Time
        0 Stop and go Greater than 175% of free flow traffic time.
        1 Heavy Between 150% and 175% of free flow traffic time.
        2 Moderate Between 125% and 150% of free flow traffic time.
        3 Free flow Less than 125% of free flow traffic time.
        255 Closed Route is unusable due to a closure or restriction on the route.
        Returns:
        The status ID.
